<div id='show_1205528233' class=''><button class="btn">Show More</button></div><div class='detail hidden' id='detail_1205528233'>
<font color='#7F7E6F'>&#62; I got to the end, hit submit and it would not let me get a cert because my email is already registered. But I don&#39;t know how to login from here. This should be more obvious at the top. I am exiting the browser and starting again.</font>
Your OIM account currently has following DN associated (and you can&#39;t re-register using the same email address)
/DC=com/DC=DigiCert-Grid/O=Open Science Grid/OU=People/CN=Eileen Berman 600
/DC=org/DC=doegrids/OU=People/CN=Eileen F. Berman 843159
Do you have either of these certificate installed on your browser? If so, you need to select it when you login to OIM. If you don&#39;t have these anymore, then you need to contact GOC and have them disabled, then you will be able to submit new user certificate request using your current email address. I think I should do 2 things here.
1) Validate email address (to see if they are already registered) before user hit submit button.
2) Show details about why they can&#39;t re-use the email address inside the form.

Yes i have the certs in the browser, and when i went back in i used them and everything went smoothly then. It would be good to let the user know that if they have an OIM account, they MUST yse it to register.  Otherwise they spend the time entering all the information only to be told they can&#39;t submit.

Thanks for addressing these!!

eileen
